The paper deals with the recovery of signals corrupted by noise, which is a common problem in signal processing. The use of sparse representations in dictionaries is a popular approach to address this problem. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely category as it deals with the study of communication and signal processing. Additionally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper presents practicable recovery algorithms. The paper also mentions applications such as image inpainting and super-resolution, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper discusses the coherence parameters of the involved dictionaries, which is a topic in sparse approximation (cs.SI).
